=========================================================
INTERVIEW READY ANSWER (30 Seconds)
=========================================================

malloc and free are C library functions used for dynamic memory
allocation and deallocation on the Heap. malloc returns raw,
uninitialized memory as a void pointer and does not call constructors,
while free simply releases memory and does not call destructors.
Therefore, in C++, new and delete are preferred because they support
object construction, destruction, and type safety.

